{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17626263","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17626263"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T16:35:31+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T16:35:31+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17063"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"17063","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/17063"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0,0.11,0.04,0.58,0.26]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"9753"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"69069"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"9753","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/9753"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17063"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"54526"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"14"},{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"913"},{"type":"tags","id":"4928"},{"type":"tags","id":"4936"},{"type":"tags","id":"4943"},{"type":"tags","id":"4944"},{"type":"tags","id":"4947"},{"type":"tags","id":"5276"},{"type":"tags","id":"10886"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"22931"},{"type":"contributions","id":"23143"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"69069","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/69069"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 45-year-old woman is diagnosed with chronic hepatitis C virus infection. She is prescribed a combination of direct-acting antiviral medications to treat this infection. \u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes the primary mechanism of action of direct-acting antivirals used to treat hepatitis C?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Stimulate host immune response","Inhibit viral entry into hepatocytes","Prevent viral assembly","Target specific viral proteins essential for replication","Block viral RNA translation"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EDirect-acting antivirals work by \u003Cstrong\u003Etargeting specific viral proteins essential for replication\u003C/strong\u003E. The main targets are the NS3/4A protease, NS5A protein, and NS5B polymerase. These viral proteins are crucial for hepatitis C virus replication and survival.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EStimulating host immune response\u003C/strong\u003E describes the mechanism of older interferon-based therapy, not direct-acting antivirals.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003ECurrent direct-acting antivirals do not target the viral entry process and therefore do not \u003Cstrong\u003Einhibit viral entry into hepatocytes. \u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EWhile some drugs may indirectly affect assembly, \u003Cstrong\u003Epreventing viral assembly\u003C/strong\u003E is not their primary mechanism of action.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EDirect-acting antivirals target post-translational viral proteins rather than \u003Cstrong\u003Eblocking viral RNA translation.\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EDifferent classes of direct-acting antivirals are typically used in combination to target multiple steps in the viral life cycle, leading to cure rates exceeding 95% in most patient populations.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Direct-acting antivirals for hepatitis C target specific viral proteins including NS3/4A protease, NS5A protein, and NS5B polymerase.","Modern hepatitis C treatment achieves cure rates over 95% with combinations of direct-acting antivirals.","Direct-acting antivirals have largely replaced interferon-based therapy due to better efficacy and fewer side effects."],"references":["Therapeutic Guidelines. Melbourne: Therapeutic Guidelines Limited. Available from: https://www.tg.org.au","Ritter J, Flower RJ (Rod J), Henderson G (Graeme), et al.\u00a0Rang and Dale\u2019s Pharmacology. Tenth edition. Elsevier; 2024.","Australian Medicines Handbook\u00a0(online). Adelaide: Australian Medicines Handbook Pty Ltd. Available from:\u00a0https://amhonline.amh.net.au/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"54526"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17063"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"54526","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/54526"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-11T09:03:45+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-11T09:04:29+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"9753"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"69069"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"14","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/14"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\udda0","name":"Infectious Diseases","synonyms":["ID"],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2021-05-21T07:51:58+09:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"